sleeping with eyes open anyone when i sleep my eyes are sometimes open a slit or more my friends have told me this a few times at sleepovers they would try and talk to me after i was already asleep because they saw my eyes were open and they thought i was still awake i was fast asleep and don't remember this at all not even seeing a blurry image another friend saw this on a long bus trip and thought i had had a seizure the doctor has even given me medicine that seals my eyes shut at night i've also tried wearing a sleep mask but it sometimes feels like my eyes are soffucating it causes me to be a very light sleeper and i was just wondering if anyone has a similar idiosyncracy and could tell me why this happens and what they do to get a good night's sleep me uncle sleeps with his eyes open and rolled back in to his head looks as if he is died it is the nerves that con troll the muscles do not con troll correctly the sleep mask does help some people but not everyone me uncle sleeps in a room that has no light coming through the windows he seems well rested to me The Shining (film) Out-of-body experience Sleep Insomnia Dream The Amber Spyglass Jon Secada Urinary incontinence Social rule W.I.T.C.H. Shaggy dog story Sleeping Murder Narcolepsy Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Sin City Sleep apnea Lycanthropy Harley Davidson and the Marlboro Man Cliff Richard 2005 trial of Michael Jackson The Ark in Space Eye Carpal tunnel syndrome Blood Simple Lucid dreaming Scenes from a Memory Traumatic brain injury Sleep debt Hide and Seek (Stargate Atlantis) The Doctor Dances The Subtle Knife Characters of The Sandman Friends Knots Landing Johnny Appleseed Mattress Samurai Deeper Kyo Princess Zelda Black Orchid (Doctor Who) The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) The Death Gate Cycle Doctor Who (Enemy Within) The Legend of Zelda series enemies Saw II The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Siesta House of M Matt Hardy Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Diabetic retinopathy Boom Town (Doctor Who)